columns.name: VARIANT_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the variant record.

columns.name: VARIANT_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The type of variation category ID for the variant.

columns.name: VARIANT_NAME
columns.description: The name assigned to the variant.

columns.name: HGVS_NAME
columns.description: The HGVS name assigned to the variant.

columns.name: GENOME_ASSEMBLY_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the reference assembly used for analyzing this variant.

columns.name: CHROMOSOME_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the chromosome the variant is found on.

columns.name: START_POSITION
columns.description: The position where the variation starts.

columns.name: STOP_POSITION
columns.description: The position where the variation ends.

columns.name: DNA_REGION
columns.description: The part of the chromosome in which the variation was found on.

columns.name: GENE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the gene name.

columns.name: GENE
columns.description: The gene name.

columns.name: GENE_SYSTEM_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the source that defined the gene name.

columns.name: TRANSCRIPT_REF_SEQ
columns.description: The external identifier defining the Transcript Reference Sequence.

columns.name: TRANSCRIPT_SYSTEM_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID for the source that defined the Transcript Reference Sequence.

columns.name: DNA_CHANGE
columns.description: The change at the DNA level relative to the Transcript Reference Sequence.

columns.name: DNA_VAR_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the DNA sequence variation type.

columns.name: AMINO_ACID_CHANGE
columns.description: The change at the amino acid (protein) level caused by the DNA change.

columns.name: PROTEIN_REF_SEQ
columns.description: The external identifier defining the Protein Reference Sequence.

columns.name: GENOMIC_REF_SEQ
columns.description: The external ID defining the Genomic Reference Sequence.

columns.name: GEN_SEQ_SYSTEM_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID for the source that defined the Genomic Reference Sequence.

columns.name: REFERENCE_ALLELE
columns.description: The DNA string in the reference sequence (Ref Allele) with which the DNA string in the test sample differs.

columns.name: OBSERVED_ALLELE
columns.description: The DNA sequence in the test sample (Ref Allele) that is different from the DNA sequence in the reference sequence (Ref Allele).

columns.name: GENOMIC_DNA_CHANGE
columns.description: The change at the DNA level relative to the Genomic Reference Sequence.

columns.name: ALLELIC_STATE_C_NAME
columns.description: The allelic state category ID for the variant.

columns.name: ALLELIC_FREQUENCY
columns.description: Reports the percentage of all of the reads at this genomic location that were represented by the given allele. For homozygotes it will be close to 100%; for heterozygotes it will be close to 50%. It can be a smaller number when there are mosaics or multiple chromosomes, or mixtures of tumor cells and normal cells. It is stored in the system as a decimal between 0 and 1 - this is calculated by dividing the percentage by 100. This field displays to end users as Variant Allele Fraction.

columns.name: CYTOGENETIC_LOC
columns.description: The cytogenetic location of the variant.

columns.name: ALLELIC_READ_DEPTH
columns.description: The read depth (or coverage) for the variant.

columns.name: PENETRANCE
columns.description: The penetrance for the variant.

columns.name: GENOMIC_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the source of the tissue for this variant.

columns.name: METHOD_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID for the type of method used to determine this variant.

columns.name: ALLELIC_PHASE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID that defines the parental set(s) of chromosomes a variant was inherited from, if any. If it was not inherited from the tested parent(s) then the category IDs of "De novo", "Not Maternal", or "Not Paternal" are used as appropriate. This field displays to end users as Parental Inheritance.
entries: 1st set of variants in cis relation to each other
2nd set of variants in cis relation to each other
3rd set of variants in cis relation to each other
4th set of variants in cis relation to each other
5th set of variants in cis relation to each other

columns.name: ALLELIC_BASIS_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the evidence on which the allelic phase (which displays to end users as parental inheritance) was concluded. This field displays to end users as Basis For Parental Inheritance.

columns.name: BOUNDARY_PRECISION
columns.description: Structural variant narrative description of the boundary precision.

columns.name: REPORTED_ACGH_RATIO
columns.description: Structural variant reported aCGH Ratio.

columns.name: ALLELE_LENGTH
columns.description: Structural variant allele length.

columns.name: INNER_START
columns.description: Structural variant inner start position.

columns.name: INNER_END
columns.description: Structural variant inner end position.

columns.name: OUTER_START
columns.description: Structural variant outer start position.

columns.name: OUTER_END
columns.description: Structural variant outer end position.

columns.name: COPY_NUMBER
columns.description: Genomic structural variant copy number as an integer. To prepare for the future deprecation of this column, your content should use either the COPY_NUMBER_LOWER or the COPY_NUMBER_UPPER columns or both.

columns.name: ASSESSMENT_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the value in LOINC 69548-6, indicating whether the variant is present, absent, indeterminate, or if no call was made.

columns.name: CLINICAL_SIGNIF_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID corresponding to the variant's classification. The name of this item was changed from clinical significance to variant classification. It appears as variant classification in end-user facing locations, but the column name remains CLINICAL_SIGNIF_C for backwards compatibility.
entries: Tier 1 or 2: Strong or potential significance

columns.name: GENOTYPE
columns.description: Genotype Name, used in combination with the column GENE (VAR 1210) to describe a Pharmacogenomic Variant.

columns.name: PGX_DRUG_METAB_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores effect on drug metabolism for a pharmacogenomic variant.

columns.name: PGX_DRUG_EFFICACY_C_NAME
columns.description: Predicted phenotype for ability of drug to bind to intended site in order to deliver intended effect.

columns.name: PGX_HIGH_RISK_C_NAME
columns.description: Predicted phenotype for risk of adverse drug reaction.

columns.name: VARIANT_FUNC_EFFECT_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID for the functional effect of the variant

columns.name: VARIANT_MOLEC_CONSEQ_C_NAME
columns.description: The molecular consequence category ID for the variant.

columns.name: MOSAICISM_C_NAME
columns.description: The mosaicism category ID for the variant record as reported by the lab.

columns.name: FRACTIONAL_COPY_NUMBER
columns.description: Genomic structural variant copy number with two decimal places of precision. To prepare for the future deprecation of this column, your content should use either the COPY_NUMBER_LOWER or the COPY_NUMBER_UPPER columns or both.

columns.name: IS_AMPLIFICATION_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the copy number variation meets the amplification threshold for this variant. 'Y' indicates that the variant has met the threshold. 'N' indicates that the variant is known to not meet the threshold. NULL might indicate that amplification does not apply, was not resulted, or could not be determined.

columns.name: GENE_ID
columns.description: Gene where the variant is located.

columns.name: GENE_ID_RECORD_SYMBOL
columns.description: The current symbol for this gene. In cases of disagreement, the current HGNC symbol will be used.

columns.name: IS_EXTERNAL_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the variant should be considered external, such as auto-reconciliation by Happy Together using data from an external organization.

columns.name: PGX_DRUG_TXPORT_C_NAME
columns.description: Predicted phenotype for drug efficacy through drug transport mechanism.

columns.name: TOTAL_REPEAT_NUMBER
columns.description: Total repeat number is the sum of all repeat numbers for one repeat expansion variant.

columns.name: PGX_ACT_SCORE_LOWER
columns.description: The lower bound of the activity score on the pharmacogenomic variant. If the activity score is a value and not a range, this will have the same value as PGX_ACT_SCORE_UPPER. If the activity score is a range without a lower bound specified, this column will contain 0.

columns.name: PGX_ACT_SCORE_UPPER
columns.description: The upper bound of the activity score on the pharmacogenomic variant. If the activity score is a value and not a range, this will have the same value as PGX_ACT_SCORE_LOWER. If the activity score is a range without an upper bound specified, this column will contain 99999.

columns.name: DISPLAY_NAME
columns.description: The name used when the variant is displayed

columns.name: ISCN_NAME
columns.description: The ISCN name assigned to the variant.

columns.name: COPY_NUMBER_LOWER
columns.description: Lower bound for the copy number of a variant.

columns.name: COPY_NUMBER_UPPER
columns.description: Upper bound for the copy number of a variant.

columns.name: VARIANT_FINDING_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores whether the variant represents an incidental finding.
